The choicest vineyards of Alsace are on the slopes of the Vosges Mountains starting from Mulhouse continu- ing north to Strasbourg. The Alsatian wines are usually named after the grape from which they are made such as Sylvaner, Riesling, Gewurztraminer, etc. Their dis- tinguishing characteristics are flowery fragrance, rela- tively dry, but fruity—at their best when drunk within five years of the vintage.
